Description: Pottery transport amphora: fractional Samian amphora with the Greek letter zeta incised pre-firing on the shoulder, and lambda on the body.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 101 (= Well 5)
Dimensions: Diameter: 11 centimetres (rim (given "12.5 x 11.0" for 'rd', rim diameter, ?))
Curator's comments: Marked in pencil "101" = indication of findspot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XVI, no. 2)
Johnston 2006b / The Delta: From Gamma to Zeta (p.27 fig.21, p.29 Table 1, no.25)
